title.2: Darkhold: Pages from the Book of Sins (1992) #1

description.3: Swooping off the pages of New Warriors! Night Thrasher and Silhouette join forces in Thrasher’s debut series. Will Gai No Don be saved from the claws of Bengal?
description.6: Ms. Marvel discovers that Mystique has killed her friend and doctor Michael Barnett! Is Carol Danvers prepared to face the full powers of Mystique and Rogue to avenge the death of Michael?
description.7: Lilith reunites with one of her lost children. Pilgrim teleports Nakota around as bait for Ghost Rider.
description.8: She-Hulk is in for a shocking surprise when she encounters Skrulls with a nasty plan!
description.9: Daredevil versus Tombstone and Izanami! The Vegas conflict continues to boil over amongst elite crime bosses.
description.10: It's a Braddock family reunion! But not all Braddocks are happy about the family, as Brian's brother Jamie has dark plans in store for the event!
description.11: It's the U-Foes and the Leader's goons versus Hulk and the Pantheon! While the fight wages on, a murderer stalks from afar!
description.14: Thor battles Bloodaxe! Mephisto makes an offer that Lady Sif can't refuse.
description.15: Jason Macendale runs a gauntlet of killers to earn back the mantle of the Hobgoblin and he now has a new target: Moon Knight!  Can Spider-Man stop the assassination of his fellow hero?
description.16: The X-Patriots, a group of Genoshan mutant refugees, set up camp in New York. X-Factor, with the aid of Val Cooper, must make a tough decision when it comes to protecting the X-Patriots' freedom.
description.17: The Infinity War reaches a fever pitch! While Magus and his doppelgangers make a bid for the Infinity Gauntlet, Sue Storm fights a war of her own - against the dark side of her psyche, Malice!
description.18: Jean Grey helps Archangel to come to terms with his new lot in life. Meanwhile, Callisto challenges Xavier to a fight to the death.
description.19: The sins of Weapon X's past are about to be paid today. Wraith, Sabretooth and Wolverine along with the shocking arrival of Silver Fox is a combustible scene that is ready to explode!
description.28: The jaw-dropping conclusion to the “Dead Man's Hand” arc. The Maggia set their sights on the Punisher and Daredevil.
description.29: Spider-Man and Solo vs. Taskmaster and his gallery of goons! Will the two heroes be able to thwart Red Skull's America Day plans?
description.30: Will the Vision be able to stop the Grim Reaper while the Avengers fight a losing battle against the Legion of the Unliving?
description.31: The final fate of Capwolf revealed! Plus: Captain America experiences the first wave of the Infinity War!
description.34: Infinity War tie-in!  Moon Knight heads back to Four Freedoms Plaza to help the heroes defeat their own doppelgangers!
description.36: Teaming up with Shang-Chi, Moon Knight faces down a horde of shrouded foes!
description.37: An all-out slugfest featuring Daredevil and Punisher against The Hand’s inner workings!
description.38: Captain America and the Punisher investigate an illegal arms ring. But what will they do when they find themselves in a fight… with each other?
description.40: Capwolf versus Cable! Who will be the Lord of the Wolves?
description.41: Can the Avengers overcome a powerful Grim Reaper and his army of the undead, a new Legion of the Unliving?
description.52: Guest-starring Daredevil! The Man Without Fear teams up with the One-Man Army to take down Chainsaw!
description.53: Will Daredevil take Las Vegas? He may have to if a slew of mob bosses continue to duke it out over the Kingpin’s empire!
description.54: An entire elderly community vanishes without a trace, and all signs point to the Crazy Gang!
description.55: Hulk and members of the Pantheon discover that the U-Foes have launched an attack! It's all-out battle between many powerful, irradiated foes! Enter the villainous mastermind, The Leader!
description.58: Will Sif and Balder be deterred on their latest mission? Thor II makes an unsavory discovery back on Earth.
description.60: Toad, a former lackey of Magneto, forms his own Brotherhood of Evil Mutants. Can it be that X-Factor has underestimated Toad's Brotherhood? X-Factor vs. a slew of dangerous mutants!
description.62: The duel with doppelgangers continues! This time, it's Johnny Storm that's forced to fight his darker half! But can he survive an entire team of X-Men duplicates?
description.63: Bishop, Colossus, and Jean Grey throwdown with the insane Morlocks in Times Square!
description.64: After mourning the loss of his past loves, Wolverine is set off on a berserker rage when he catches the scent of his love's killer. Plus, Sabretooth tangles with a S.H.I.V.A robot in NYC.
description.65: Wolverine's memories continue to reveal themselves a little at a time, but which are real and which have been implanted? And can he focus on the adversary right in front of him that is John Wraith? When Wolverine sees who John Wraith has captive, that will command all of Wolverine's attention.
description.69: Peter Parker, meet your parents! Peter must confront his past when his parents arrive at Aunt May's home after years of being believed dead. But will Richard and Mary Parker's story check out? And why is Spider-Man tracking down Red Skull for answers?
description.70: When the Grim Reaper is able to acquire an ancient power, he traps the Avengers in another dimension. Will Earth's Mightest Heroes be able to stop this powered-up Grim Reaper?
description.71: Prepare for the Wolfpack! Capwolf rallies together a team of feral beast to stop Druid from using the moonstone's magic to solidify his own powers! But find out what happens when Capwolf is too late!
description.75: While Johnny is battling the cyborg Steel Vengeance, Ghost Rider awakens from his coma with knowledge on Dan Ketch!
description.76: In search for her missing fiancée, Morbius, Martine Bancroft seeks the aid of Ghost Rider, Johnny Blaze, and Dr. Langford. When things take a turn for the worse, Martine learns the true color of her fiancée…blood red!
description.77: Weezi returns to the She-Hulk storyline to save Jen from a fate worse than death!
description.81: Infinity War tie-in!  Moon Knight's doppelganger levels up by absorbing Moon Knights across the multiverse and dubs himself Moon Shade.  What can our hero Marc Spector do to stop this power mad doppelganger?
description.86: Nomad and Bucky link up with the Punisher in Part 4 of “Dead Man's Hand.”
description.87: It's man versus wolf as Captain America is turned into a werewolf!
description.88: Raza is looking to collect the bounty on the Black Knight in exchange for information on his missing son, but just how far will he go in battle against the Avengers to secure what he needs?
description.89: Captured by the'Emperor,'Leia'discovers that he holds hostage an even greater treasure: a mysterious and intelligent artifact called the'Jedi'Holocron. With both the Holocron and'Luke Skywalker'under his control, there's no limit to what the'Emperor'can do!'
description.98: How the mighty Kingpin has fallen as New York’s major crime players divvy up his immense empire. Matt Murdock and Foggy Nelson head to Las Vegas to meet with potential clients.
description.99: Brian reveals to Meggan his early days of training to be a hero, on his way to becoming Captain Britain!

1.text: The team goes to Almagordo to save Xavier from Hazard.

2.text: Physician Victoria Montesi uncovers her ties to an arcane evil. Guest-starring Ghost Rider!

3.text: Swooping off the pages of New Warriors! Night Thrasher and Silhouette join forces in Thrasher’s debut series. Will Gai No Don be saved from the claws of Bengal?

4.text: Free from his bonds at a corrupt laboratory, Luke Cage hunts down Hardcore to have him answer for his misdeeds! A super-powered struggle in the mighty Marvel manner!

5.text: The Guardians witness some alien anomalies in battle with the Masters of Evil. Who or what are these doppelgänger beings attacking both sides? And what can stop their constant duplication? The Guardians and Masters of Evil vs. lookalike extraterrestrials!

6.text: Ms. Marvel discovers that Mystique has killed her friend and doctor Michael Barnett! Is Carol Danvers prepared to face the full powers of Mystique and Rogue to avenge the death of Michael?

7.text: Lilith reunites with one of her lost children. Pilgrim teleports Nakota around as bait for Ghost Rider.

8.text: She-Hulk is in for a shocking surprise when she encounters Skrulls with a nasty plan!

12.text: At Tony Stark's funeral, James Rhodes faces his first threat at the new Iron Man: the combined might of Spymaster, Whiplash, Blizzard and the Beetle! Plus: his body frozen and secretly still alive, Stark faces the truth behind his alcoholism!  (Originally published as IRON MAN (1992) #285)

19.text: The sins of Weapon X's past are about to be paid today. Wraith, Sabretooth and Wolverine along with the shocking arrival of Silver Fox is a combustible scene that is ready to explode!

23.text: X-Force goes head to head with Crule and learns that they must save their former teammate Sunspot. Meanwhile, the true identity of Domino is finally revealed!

27.text: Infinity War crossover! Doctor Strange, alongside Scarlet Witch, Dr. Druid, and the Sleepwalker, try to free Earth from its paralysis!

33.text: Back in the U.S. of A! Frank Castle finds America and his city in not quite the same shape as he left it…

35.text: Introducing the heroism of Turbo and the villainy of Cardinal! Plus, it's Namorita vs. the Sea Urchin: Round 2!

42.text: The FINAL conflict of the Eurohit saga! Will it be good or evil that prospers?

43.text: The Marvel heroes are fighting a war on two fronts while the Magus schemes his way to total domination. Is the only way to save the universe...the Infinity Gauntlet?!
The Marvel heroes are fighting a war on two fronts while the Magus schemes his way to total domination. Is the only way to save the universe...the Infinity Gauntlet?!

44.text: Wolverine discovers a dark secret from Professor Xavier’s past.

45.text: Under attack by S.H.I.E.L.D. agents, X-Force must figure out a way to escape from the battle unscathed. Recovering from the blast, Cable and Domino make their way to Cable's secret lair and prepare to rescue the rest of the team.

51.text: After Galactus’ ship is destroyed, Death takes Doctor Strange on a tour of his family member’s deaths.

53.text: Will Daredevil take Las Vegas? He may have to if a slew of mob bosses continue to duke it out over the Kingpin’s empire!

56.text: Tony Stark is dead! When the legacies of the Iron Man and Stark Enterprises are left in the hands of Jim Rhodes, Iron Man's longtime ally wonders whether he has what it takes to fill the shoes of his former boss! Featuring Doctor Doom and the Avengers!  (Originally published as IRON MAN (1992) #284)

72.text: Luke Cage has an unwelcome blast from the past while imprisoned at a facility that’s experimenting with the Power Man serum! Innocent civilians are put through inhumane testing. Will a new generation of impenetrable Power Men and Women see the light of day? Not if Cage can help it!

73.text: Infinity War tie-in. The Masters of Evil have launched their attack on Earth’s Mightiest Heroes. Luckily the Guardians are at Avengers Mansion- and just in time too!

74.text: A retrospective issue on the Guardians’ earliest adventures! How did Replica become a Guardian? And why does Yondu want to leave the team?

75.text: While Johnny is battling the cyborg Steel Vengeance, Ghost Rider awakens from his coma with knowledge on Dan Ketch!

76.text: In search for her missing fiancée, Morbius, Martine Bancroft seeks the aid of Ghost Rider, Johnny Blaze, and Dr. Langford. When things take a turn for the worse, Martine learns the true color of her fiancée…blood red!

77.text: Weezi returns to the She-Hulk storyline to save Jen from a fate worse than death!

78.text: BIOHAZARD AGENDA PART 4 Is this the end of the road for Deathlok? Siege and Deathlok face off against their worst enemy yet!

79.text: Classic Star Wars features the adventures of everyone's favorite Rebels during the period between the first and second Star Wars films. In this issue, Darth Vader plots new ways to trip up the Rebels, but a turncoat Admiral may thwart his plans. Meanwhile, Luke, Leia, Han, and Chewie make good their escape from a bounty hunter, only to run afoul of the Imperial fleet!

80.text: Punisher schedules a meeting with local mob leaders. One must wonder if the meeting will go how they expect it to with Frank Castle at the head of the table…

82.text: Speedballs’s doppelganger attacks Robbie…followed up by his family!

85.text: A flashback to Nick Fury's time as a member of the U.S. Army in the midst of a bloody battle!

90.text: Punisher takes to Spain to alert them on Snakebite's plans before it's too late!

91.text: After storming Tolliver's base, X-Force must race against the clock in order to get out alive. With the team entering into the fray, Domino's intentions are further questioned.

93.text: Magus's plan for domination hits a deadly new level.  And when the heroes track down the cause of the mayhem, they come face to face with Thanos and Warlock and the Infinity Watch.  Fight!
Magus's plan for domination hits a deadly new level.  And when the heroes track down the cause of the mayhem, they come face to face with Thanos and Warlock and the Infinity Watch.  Fight!

94.text: Xavier and Psylocke use their psychic abilities to take out Mojo!

95.text: Luke and Leia embark on a scouting mission, are pursued by Imperial troops, and fall into the clutches of a bounty hunter whose real target is Han Solo! Whew!

96.text: Four Deathlok stories combined in one issue! In his first annual, Michael Collins faces some harsh truths about his human family. Deathlok discovers Harlan Ryker’s journal. Could this discovery be the key to becoming a human once again?

97.text: BIOHAZARD AGENDA PART 3 Deathlok will stop at nothing to live again as a human man. But what strange force is preventing his end goal? And could this be the resurrection of John Kelly, the first Deathlok?

98.text: How the mighty Kingpin has fallen as New York’s major crime players divvy up his immense empire. Matt Murdock and Foggy Nelson head to Las Vegas to meet with potential clients.
